The update problem gives us some insight about the general problem in the database. We can see that the problem with the database is not a duplicate problem is a record situation.

  • Duplicates inside static data:

    • There wer duplicated observations inside static data, probably in Lost data from China (CN).

  • Duplicates bewteen static data and dynamic data:

    • Probably Lost data from China (CN) had observations already present in Am current data (BecharaReport API).

  • Duplicated paths in Meditation table (MT)

    • MT table is been joined with Am data by the audio path (.ogg file) to get more information about the meditation characteristics. Although there are duplicate paths in MT data (for example, a same audio log is repeated in different languages). This is generating duplicates when joined.

Record situation

Understanding the database as a record data can help us to solve the majority of the problems in the database.

A solution for the record situation involves the following indications:

  1. Rather than keep one of the duplicates randomnly, we can keep the latest observation of the recorded data.

    1. To know the latest observation in the data, we need a unique id for each observation.

    2. This approach can solve the upper-lower case problem, rounding problem, and update problem.

  2. Although only applying the solution of the latest observation doesn’t solve the computing problem. It’s necessary to ensure that the preserved observation has the correct computed_stress_pre, computed_stress_post and not only -1 when is not the case.
